Related

Stats

Historical

Biography

2016-17 as a Senior (through 3/20/17):

Preseason Honorable Mention All-CAA

Leads JMU with 25 blocks

Has played in 18 games, starting 12

Exploded for 15-point, 17-rebound performance vs. Elon on 1/14/17

Will miss remainder of season with injury

2015-16 as a Junior:

Named to the Preseason All-CAA Second Team

Missed the first two games of the season with a foot injury, but has played in all 26 games with 25 starts since returning

Put together a monster 23-point, 15-rebound double-double in 28 minutes against Marshall

Scored a career-high 26 points on 13 of 19 shooting against Northeastern on Feb. 18

Has five double-double performances on the season including three in a five game span from Feb. 4 through Feb. 18.

Ranks first on the Dukes with 6.8 rebounds per game, while providing 9.3 points per game through March 15, 2016

Also leads the Dukes in blocks with 1.3 per game, which is good for second overall in the CAA

Leads all Dukes in field goal percentage and ranks fourth overall in the CAA (among players with at least 50 attempts) at 54.2% through March 15, 2016

2014-15 as a Sophomore:

Third Team All-CAA

CAA All-Defensive Team, the first member from JMU in 20 years

Started all 33 games for JMU as a sophomore, averaging 25.2 minutes per game

Finished the year averaging 11.4 points and 6.0 rebounds per game

Shot 57.8 percent (137-237) on field goals and 67.3 percent (101-150) on free throws

Posted 20 double-digit scoring efforts and 14 performances with six rebounds or more

Scored at least three points in every contest

Led CAA play with a 60.3 field goal percentage and 1.3 blocks per game

Career-high 21 points against College of Charleston (Feb. 22)

Notched first career double-doubles with 10 points, 10 boards against Campbell (12/2) and 14 points, 10 boards against Delaware (2/10)

Scored 20 points and grabbed six rebounds in win over Colgate (11/24)

Did not play less than 15 minutes in any contest

2013-2014 as a Freshman:

Finished the season averaging 11.7 minutes per game to go with averages of 2.3 points, 2.5 rebounds and 0.54 blocks in addition to a field goal percentage of .463

Recorded one game of ten or more points and one game of eight or more rebounds

Six rebounds and two blocks in JMU debut at Virginia

First collegiate points with two free throws vs. Milwaukee

Career high of seven points in Towson road loss

Had 33 total season points before breaking through with JMU's third double-double of the season with 15 points and 13 rebounds in 26 minutes at Delaware. Was 5-for-9 from the field and 5-for-5 at the foul line

Seven points in home win over UNCW to cap CAA Rookie of the Week set of three games

Before College:

Played for head coach Gregg Downer and Lower Merion High School

Led the Aces to a 30-3 record and the PIAA Class AAAA state title after averaging 11.3 points, 9.4 rebounds and 4.1 blocks as a senior

Collected 10 points and seven boards in Hershey’s Giant Center in 63-47 state title upset of Chester, halting the Clippers’ streak of 78 straight wins vs. Pennsylvania foes

Lower Merion’s state title was the program’s second since Kobe Bryant led the Aces in 1996 (also 2006)

Averaged 14 points, 12 rebounds and 4.9 blocks during Lower Merion’s playoff run

Second Team All-State and All-Southeastern Pa.

First Team All-Central League and First Team All-Main Line

Standout senior performances included 15 points, 12 rebounds and seven blocks to earn MVP honors of the Cancer Research Classic (W. Va.), tournament MVP honors at the Kobe Bryant Classic with 29 points, 29 boards and 12 blocks as well as career highs of 28 points and 18 rebounds in a Feb. 4 win over Radnor

First career basketball start came as a high school junior with 17 points and 10 rebounds in PIAA round of 16 in 2012 state playoffs

Spent entire life as a soccer player until the 2010 Haiti Earthquake, when he moved to Philadelphia and picked up a basketball for the first time

Personal:

Son of Cassandra Derrosiers

Half-brother of Samuel Dalembert, who will begin his 13th NBA season in 2014-15 with his sixth different team, the New York Knicks.

Samuel Dalembert was a member of the Philadelphia 76ers when the 2010 Haiti Earthquake occurred, prompting him to aid Yohanny and sister Severine to relocate to Philadelphia.

Majoring in sport and recreation management

Quick Hits with Yohanny:

Best Part about being at JMU: The campus

Best part about playing for Coach Brady: He develops his players

Place in the CAA you're most looking to travel to: Delaware

Favorite NBA player: Kevin Garnett

What it will take to win the CAA and make the NCAA Tournament: Be all about JMU Basketball
